        public VirtualMachineClassesTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setCpuReservation(java.lang.Long cpuReservation)
        Deprecated. As of release vSphere API 8.0.2.0. Use CPU allocation in VirtualMachineClassesTypes.CreateSpec.getConfigSpec() instead to reserve CPUs for a virtual machine. If null, no CPU reservation is requested for the virtual machine.
        The percentage of total available CPUs reserved for a virtual machine. We multiply this percentage by the minimum frequency amongst all the cluster nodes to get the CPU reservation that is specified to vSphere in MHz. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100.
        Parameters:
        cpuReservation - New value for the property.

        The percentage of available memory reserved for a virtual machine of this class. Memory reservation must be set to 100% for VM class with vGPU or Dynamic DirectPath I/O devices. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100.
